76561198128696082,Recommended,254820,29737509,Posted: 6 February,all,Varathius,"""Command APC under fire by friendly units""...All you Ground Control vets could not sleep one night without hearing the same friendly fire warning over and over again, yet, we never lost one unit due to friendly fire! Correct, Ground Control is back you chaps and chapettes, and it works flawlessly on Windows 10 I might add.For you fresh potential volunteer commanders for the Crayven Corporation, rest assure, you will meet battle where advanced battle tactics need to be used! You do not construct bases, but you manage Dropships in terms of what units you will use, and as you progress, the more units become available, but fact of the matter is, you choose what you want. Do you want to use Jaeger Special Forces recon troops to scout the area undetected to then sneak your artillery nearby to blow everything to kingdom come? Or do you prefer to rush into an enemy heavily defended base with scout vehicles to quickly take out the anti-air defenses, so that you can pull out in time and have your aerodynes fly into the base and bomb it all to ashes without any air defenses. Or perhaps, do you want to roll into the bases with a mix of heavy guns and marines? YOU DECIDE ! This is Gound Control !This package contains the main campaign plus the expansion pack (known as DLC today). The main campaign takes you in command of the Crayven Corporation (Crays) and the Order of the dawn (Dawnies). Playing the game on normal difficulty will take you approx. 10 hours for the Crayven Corporation Campaign, and another 8 for the Dawnie campaign. 18-20 hours of missions !! And this without the expansion pack, because with the expansion pack, add another 15 hours, so you are looking at a solid 32-35 hours of Campaign missions on the normal difficulty setting, for this low price! And keep in mind, this is one of the most amazing RTS games ever made, and there is a Ground Control 2 as well !!! (sold separately).With the Crayven campaign you mostly assume traditional missions of base destructions, but once you play for the Dawnies, expect more fast paced guerrilla warfare and hit and run tactics, because you are fighting outnumbered most of the times with inferior equipment because hey, the Crays did kick your♥♥♥♥♥just shortly before so don't expect it to be easy!Despite the somewhat outdated graphics the explosions and gun fire etc effects as still beautiful. There are some guys that still play multiplayer, but google it as you will find all the info there (some dedicated servers are still up with plenty of players).Pros:- Fun and amazing missions!- Great visuals despite aged graphics- Great sound and amazing battle soundtracks- Awesome Units with micromanaging secondary and tertiary abilities during combat- Dropship unit loadout customization- Plenty of hours of gameplay- Low price- Classic RTS game (top 5 next to Old westwood studios C&C games, Homeworld, etc), a must have!- Entertaining briefing/debriefing and lore (story)- 40+ missions!!!- Works flawlessly on Windows 10- Units have weakspots (rear takes more damage on tanks, etc).- Many fun units to choose from and play- Battle formations to choose from- Can use terrain and shadows etc as a tactical advantage!!!- Great tutorialCons:- Cannot save during game. Play it on LIGHT or EASY for the first time since normal is like a game on Hard today.- No skirmish mode (Single player campaign only and for Multiplayer, find info out of game first how to join!)- Micromanaging units during intense combat can be frustrating at times due to game mechanics. Units need a lot of room to pass each other, they easily get stuck with each other showing their rear to the enemy and taking much more damage. Big chance to lose your command APC that way =Mission failure.- Constant friendly fire messages ""Squad 1 taking friendly fire"" etc, etc, however, friendly fire is mitigated significantly, you only take tiny damage but still very annoying to hear those messages all the time. Terrain often does not give enough room to prevent friendly fire, thus those warnings and friendly fire cannot be avoided.If you are an old school or newbro RTS fan, you MUST get this game at all costs, and after you beat this game and its Dark Conspiracy expansion pack (included in bundle), you must play Ground Control 2.DISMISSED !"
