,Not Recommended,254820,29924743,Posted: 14 February,all,PurpleXVI,"Not as good as nostalgia made me remember it.In my memories, Ground Control was essentially sci-fi Myth, but it turns out I was remembering wrong. Myth had its share of issues, but it didn't have the mess of slow unit responses, terrible unit AI(I can't count the number of times that half my troops' fire, or their special attacks, were wasted because the front lines hit the back lines, or blasted away into terrain rather than moving an inch right or left) and incredibly unclear fields of view(you'll only know how far your units can actually see when something suddenly pops into view. A visible field of view or obscuring fog of war would have done wonders).The writing's decent, though for some reason it feels like they switched VA's for established characters between GC1 and Dark Conspiracy. But ultimately the game is 95% gameplay, and 5% story, so even good writing can't really bouy poor gameplay.Also kinda buggy, with missions that sometimes arbitrarily seeming not to finish/progress, forcing you to replay them, and with Dark Conspiracy forgetting my campaign progress when I exit. Not too great.The soundtrack is excellent, though. Very good at setting a mood."
