76561197962139320,Not Recommended,254820,34806735,Posted: 7 September,all,Ravanger,"No problems on a win 7 laptop, though the environment is a little blurry, but what do you expect for a game made in 2000. A RTS with no base building. One good thing about this game is that you can slightly configure the units you want to bring along on your mission. The bad thing is that it doesn't save your load out, so you have to keep reconfiguring each time. At most you will control up to 13 fighting units, though the air units are kinda useless since they die easily. I would say this was a great game for 2000, but not so much today. I think it is a good deal for $1.50, but playing the game, I was more frustrated with it than having fun. I had a hard time moving my army in formation, since they like to dance around each other. I was also annoyed by the indestructible walls and the amount of friendly fire. The game is challenging, though that might be because you can't save in game and can't give orders while in pause. Rate 4.5/10."
